(1) Two members appointed by the mayor of the town of Ferriday.
(2) Two members appointed by the governing authority of the town of Ferriday.
(3) One member appointed by the chief executive officer of Concordia Bank & Trust.
(4) One member appointed by the chief executive officer of Delta Bank.
(5) One member appointed by the governing board of the Delta Museum who shall be
a representative of the museum.
Proposed law removes the appointments granted to the chief executive officer of Concordia
Bank & Trust and the chief executive officer of Delta Bank. Grants one appointment each
to the member of the La. House of Representatives who represents District No. 21, the
member of the La. Senate who represents District No. 34, the Concordia Parish Sheriff's
Department, and the governing board of Delta Recreation. Proposed law increases the board
membership from seven to nine.
Proposed law provides that members serve three-year staggered terms.
Proposed law retains present law and provides for the initial terms of the four newly
appointed board members. Provides that the terms of the one member appointed by the chief
executive officer of Concordia Bank and the one member appointed by the chief executive
officer of Delta Bank shall terminate on the effective date of proposed law. Provides that
the members shall remain in office until their successors are appointed and take office.
Additionally provides that the two members appointed by mayor of the town of Ferriday, the
two members appointed by the governing authority of the town of Ferriday, and the one
member appointed by the governing board of the Delta Museum shall continue to serve until
the expiration of their terms.
Proposed law authorizes the officers of the Concordia Parish Sheriff's Department to patrol
the area included within the boundaries of the district and to make arrests within the area.
Provides that the officers shall no longer be authorized to patrol the area included within the
boundaries of the district or make arrests in the area if the district ceases to exist.
(Amends R.S. 33:2740.70.6(B), (D)(1)(intro. para.), (c), and (d) and (2), and (I); Adds R.S.
33:2740.70.6(D)(1)(f) and (g) and (J))
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Municipal, Parochial
and Cultural Affairs to the original bill:
1. Make changes to the composition of the board.
2. Add provisions that provide for the initial terms of certain board members.
3. Add provisions that provide that the terms of certain board members shall
terminate on the effective date of proposed law.
4. Add provisions that provide that certain board members shall continue to serve
until the expiration of their terms.
5. Authorize the officers of the Concordia Parish Sheriff's Department to patrol the
area included within the boundaries of the district and to make arrests in the area.
